modules.description: This module defines a configuration structure for IP geolocation lookups, containing fields for API key, data format, source URL, and source version. It provides the `init` function to initialize the configuration with a given API key. Concrete use cases include setting up API access parameters for querying IP address metadata from a remote service.

This module performs WHOIS lookups for IP addresses using a provided configuration, returning a status code and JSON response. It works with IP address strings and configuration data, extracting domain names and extensions from IP-related information. Concrete use cases include geolocation analysis and network troubleshooting based on IP metadata.

This module handles IP geolocation lookups by initializing API configurations and performing WHOIS queries. It works with IP address strings and configuration records containing API keys and source metadata. Use cases include retrieving geolocation data for network diagnostics and domain information extraction from IP addresses.
